sfPhpDoc plugin
===============

The `sfPhpDocPlugin` is a symfony plugin that provides you with a task to
generate your sourcecode documentation via PhpDoc.

You still need to install phpdoc before you can use this plugin!

Installation
------------

  * Install the plugin via the subversion repository.

  * Copy the included phpdoc.ini into your projects config folder.

        $ cp plugins/sfPhpDocPlugin/config/phpdoc.ini config/phpdoc.ini

Configuration
-------------

  * You can edit the phpdoc.ini using the phpdoc command line options. You can
    get the options via the phpdoc command.

        $ phpdoc -h

Usage
-----

  * Execute the task bundled with the plugin. It will generate the documentation
    in your projects doc directory.

        $ ./symfony generate:phpdoc
